I use the popular English cuss words quite frequently in my own language (Dutch). I don't use them much in English, probably because the way I learned it (in school) and had to use English (in professional reports). It's not a concious choice to use them, it's just something I got used to. Yes, sometimes I use them to insult people, when I think they deserve it (or when I am being unreasonable, whatever). Sometimes I don't use them for that at all, that doesn't mean I use them to look cool or whatever. People around me used them and I started to use them to /shrug<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And Merharra, you're already at the top of the game, got pretty much everything you can 'til Fantasy gets into the next level of raiding. You're already level 65...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Nope, except my Earring of Endless Speed all that I was wearing was essentially gear Fantasy could get pre-Vindicator. We killed Vindicator in March/April and I left Fantasy in October/November. Just accept it, some people LIKE raiding. What my level has got to do with anything, I do not know.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I tried and tried to get people to go dungeon crawling while I was leveling up, but to keep pace with my friends in game (who had more time then me) I had to go to the standard places to level.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes, leveling is a pain like that. But some people are willing to do that in order to get higher and thus being able to do more things. That seems silly, considering it is just a game, but maybe that proofs that Everquest is more than a game. For people blessed with friends they group with regularly, leveling is actually quite fun. Everquest wasn't fun to you, but that doesn't mean others can't have fun - Everquest obviously isn't for everyone.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And raiding is boring. I don't know about Luclin boss mobs, but Kael/Vindi/HoT were quite boring. You sit in one spot and wait for monks to come to you. Then you wait for tank to call assist. Then you run in and stab it 'til it's dead.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Correction : Raiding is boring to YOU. HoT was quite boring, I agree. I loved Vindi hits or any of the big bosses. I never grew tired of that. But, to be honest, if I were a rogue, I would think it would be pretty boring too. I think that goes for every class whose job it is to just melee a mob and not to get agro. Then again, you also have hits to mobs like Itraer Vius, it is actually challenging to make it to the mob (lots of non-stunnable gaters) and the fight itself is interesting to. I also know people used to like the Rhag 1 / 2 fights, since you have to fight to the mobs. Fights like that will be less fun if the mobs you have to fight through become to easy. <br>
<br>
We actually did plow through HoT once, it was just as boring =P I do agree, guilds prefer to keep it safe, but be honest, an hour CR isn't fun either.<br>
<br>
Sorry to use quotes so much, but there were many topics to touch on =P <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26345">Merrahar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
